  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p>The Three Valleys spans across 600 kilometres of slopes and offers the highest number of interconnected runs in Europe. Although <a data-udi="umb://document/50690c0f70c74050930d18799cab6fa8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/50690c0f70c74050930d18799cab6fa8}" title="Val Thorens">Val Thorens</a>, <a data-udi="umb://document/9e7d0f01e7964af0b7ee7c501cb0e893" href="/{localLink:umb://document/9e7d0f01e7964af0b7ee7c501cb0e893}" title="Courchevel">Courchevel</a>, <a data-udi="umb://document/870730cefeb2441dab9ccfec19c2fe88" href="/{localLink:umb://document/870730cefeb2441dab9ccfec19c2fe88}" title="Meribel">Meribel</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/4eae720ba8984d83a83f530983b4b6f8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4eae720ba8984d83a83f530983b4b6f8}" title="Les Menuires">Les Menuires</a> all have something unique to offer, they are all linked through this large ski area, allowing you the opportunity to explore the whole of the Three Valleys despite where you choice to stay - so really you're spoilt for choice! </p>]]></generalInformation>
